<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://englishspellingproblems.blogspot.com"><i>EnglishSpellingProblems</i> blog by Masha Bell</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://improvingenglishspelling.blogspot.com/2010/09/index.html"><i>Improving English Spelling</i> Blog by Masha Bell</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.economist.com/blogs/johnson/2010/09/spelling_reform">"Spelling reform: It didn't go so well in Germany"</a> article in the Economist's <i>Johnson</i> Blog about spelling reform</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.nooalf.com">The Nooalf Revolution</a> Provides an English-based international spelling system.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.wyrdplay.org/reform-files.html">Wyrdplay.org</a> has an extensive list of current spelling reform proposals.</li>
</ul>


